Here's how to implement auto-playing through multiple videos:

1. Add urlIdx tracking in GradebookUi
2. Add method to play next video
3. Register onEnd callback when initializing YouTube player
4. Update video player initialization to handle urlIdx

### /Users/kris/code/match-grader/src/tsModules/match-grader/gradebook_ui.ts

```typescript
// filepath: /Users/kris/code/match-grader/src/tsModules/match-grader/gradebook_ui.ts
export class GradebookUi extends HTMLElement {
  private youtubePlayerUi: YoutubePlayerUi = new YoutubePlayerUi;
  private currentUrlIdx = 0;
  // ...existing code...

  private updateYoutubePlayer() {
    const urls = this.gradebookMgr.project.matchData.urls;
    if (urls.length < 1) {
      return;
    }
    const {success, id} = extractYoutubeId(urls[this.currentUrlIdx]);
    if (!success) {
      return;
    }
    this.youtubePlayerUi.initYoutubePlayer(id);
    this.youtubePlayerUi.onEnd(() => {
      if (this.currentUrlIdx < urls.length - 1) {
        this.currentUrlIdx++;
        this.updateYoutubePlayer();
      }
    });
  }

  private obtainYoutubeUrl() {
    const url = prompt('Enter url');
    if (!url) {
      return;
    }
    const res = extractYoutubeId(url);
    if (!res.success) {
      return;
    }
    this.gradebookMgr.project.matchData.urls.push(url);
    if (this.gradebookMgr.project.matchData.urls.length === 1) {
      // Only update player for first video, subsequent ones will play automatically
      this.updateYoutubePlayer();
    }
  }

  // ...existing code...
}
```

Now when one video finishes:
1. The player will check if there are more videos in the urls array
2. If there are, it will increment currentUrlIdx and load the next video
3. Each video will chain to the next one until all videos have been played

The obtainYoutubeUrl method has been updated to only initialize the player for the first video added, since subsequent videos will play automatically through the onEnd callback.

